    #blablabla
      %p
        Hi, I'm Alessandro, a
        = succeed "." do
          %span.important full stack Web developer
        I started programming on my own during high school, with Visual Basic on Windows 98SE. Meh. That's a big jump being working with Ruby and Web now, more than 10 years later, but the outcome for me is the same as when I started: I
        = succeed "." do
          %span.important create something
        And something
        = succeed "." do
          %span.important great
      %p
        I live in London and work as a freelance Ruby and Rails developer, baking out solutions for my customers. Being a supporter of the Agile principles I like to
        %span.important communicate
        with people to solve their problems. I use also the best methodologies and technologies of present and future, as long as it is possible, because I think
        %span.important innovation
        is what makes every day different from the previous one (see this #{link_to 'video of the mythical Jean-Claude Biver', 'http://liftconference.com/lift11/program/talk/anonymous-importance-innovation', :target => 'blank'} to see what I mean).
      %p
        I like entrepreneurship, startups, house music, bartending, art, a lot of sports and culture in general!
